(1) 547 East 54th Street, at the N.E. corner of Canarsie Ave., show- ing the J.W. Anderson house. Mr Anderson had his blacksmith shop across the road, at the S.W. corner in 1857. Jackson Ryder owned this house at a later date. It was demolished in 1929.

1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, from a slightly different angle. Note the addition of a summer porch. On the right appears No. 5403 Beverly Road.

March 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3) The same, in a decrepit state, just prior to demolition.

June 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster collection.

(4) A view of the wings and additions at its rear.

June 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
